oyee s home address  Cadet Assistant and College Work Study checks are mailed to cadet post office boxes  and to home addresses during breaks    50120  Electronic Direct Deposit Return to top  Electronic direct deposit is mandatory for new full time employees Part time employees  including cadets  are highly encouraged to participate in direct deposit  Employees may utilize up to four separate fixed direct deposit accounts in addition to their regular direct deposit account The fixed direct deposits may be at different financial institutions from the regular direct deposit account  Employees shall notify the payroll section immediately of changes to their financial institution or account number  In this case  the employee shall complete a new Employee Direct Deposit Authorization Form  The Employee Electronic Direct Deposit Advice provided by the Comptroller s Office is a non negotiable document that shows  1  the amount of net pay  2  bank name s  and 3  the last four digits of bank account number s This advice provides the same deduction information as a  regular  paycheck stub    50130  New Employees Return to top  All new employees shall complete W 4 and VA 4 Forms and submit them to the Comptroller s Office New full time employees shall also complete health care  retirement  and life insurance forms  These forms are available from Human Resources  Direct deposit is mandatory for new full time employees  therefore  all new full time employees shall also complete the Employee Electronic Direct Deposit Authorization form    50140 Hourly Employee Time Sheets Return to top  Departments shall submit directly to the Comptroller s Office time sheets for hourly employees Pay periods run from 1st through the 15th and the 16th through the 31st of each month  The payday for hours worked the 1st through the 15th will be the 1st of the following month and the payday for hours worked the 16th through the 31st will be the 16th of the following month  VMI shall not pay hourly employees for estimated hours worked  thus all time sheets shall reflect actual hours worked Time sheets are due in the Comptroller s Office by 1700 Hours on the second business day after the end of the pay period  The departments shall prepare the time sheets in ink  furthermore  both the employee and his her supervisor shall sign the time sheet in ink  If any changes are made to a time sheet  both the employee and the supervisor must initial the correction  Failure to follow these procedures may result in a delay in payment  Cadet Assistants and College Work Study Cadets are also paid by the hour but are handled differently For employment of a cadet  please contact the Office of Career Services for the proper procedures    50150  Payroll Changes Return to top  Payrolls are scheduled to allow adequate time for processing  Employees requesting changes in miscellaneous deductions  marital status  or dependents claimed shall submit the changes to the Comptroller s Office by the 1st of the month for the 1st through the 15th payroll and by the 16th of the month for the 16th through the 31st payroll  Employees shall submit these changes directly to the Comptroller s Office  Individuals desiring to start or change a tax shelter shall submit them to Human Resources  The Director of Auxiliary Services shall approve all post housing rent notices and changes before any change can be made on the payroll  Human Resources shall notify the Comptroller s Office of any time loss  code changes  pay increases or decreases that may affect the employee during a given pay period  In some cases of time loss and if the employee is not working  then VMI will hold the paycheck or stop the direct deposit  in such cases  VMI will only pay the employee the actual amount due    50210  Miscellaneous Payroll Deductions Return to top  The payroll system allows VMI to withhold miscellaneous payroll deductions from employees  pay and distribute them to the proper vendor The following is a list of current payroll deductions  Pre Tax Deductions  Flex Dependent Flex Medical Health Insurance   Tax Sheltered Annuities  American Express Financial Advisors Commonwealth of Virginia Deferred Compensation Plan Diversified Investment Advisors Equitable Fidelity Retirement Services Lincoln National Life Insurance Company Met Life New York Life T Rowe Price Teachers Insurance and Annuity Association USAA Variable Annuity Life Insurance Company Virginia Retirement Specialists  Inc    After Tax Deductions  AFLAC Insurance Aetna Long Term Care Insurance Aetna Long Term Care Insurance Combined Virginia Campaign Flex Administrative Fee Guardian Disability Insurance Rent  Post Housing Only  U S  Savings Bonds Virginia Governmental Employees Association Virginia Prepaid Education Program VMI Foundation VMI Keydet Club VRS Optional Life Insurance  50220  W 2 Information Return to top  W 2 forms are required by law to be distributed by 31 January of each year  VMI mails W 2 forms to employees  home addresses  Unofficial copies of W 2s may also be viewed on PostView  Payroll Alumni Payroll Deduct Form  Electronic Direct Dep Form  Fed W 4 Form  Hourly Timesheet  Payroll Ded Auth Form  VA 4 State Tax Form  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museu